  <div class="image-caption">Retina Display Speed ups! (the video thumbnail is even cringier... you're welcome)</div>

<p>Do you have a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Retina_display">Retina Display</a> and are constantly frustrated about low FPS desktop applications?</p>

<p>This is a big issue if you’re a <a href="https://www.reaper.fm">Reaper</a> or <a href="https://www.tracktion.com/products/waveform">Waveform</a> user (as of the writing of this post).</p>

<p>Let me show you how to get 10-15 extra FPS with little lost.</p>

<p>(Rorry for the clickbait title, I think it’s funny.)</p>

<!--more-->

<p><strong>If you have any questions or comments, please comment below! I read every comment and respond to most.</strong> No registration is necessary to comment, so don’t be shy.</p>

<h1 class="no_toc" id="contents">Contents</h1>
<ul id="markdown-toc">
